Package: vldaft
Title: Non-Proportional Hazards Accelerated Failure Time Regression
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Keaven", "Anderson", , "keaven_anderson@merck.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"))
    )
Description: Fits the Anderson (1991) accelerated failure time regression
    model where both location and scale are functions of covariates, and
    scale can depend on location via a polynomial in the linear predictor.
    Supports Weibull, logistic, normal, Cauchy, and gamma error
    distributions with right censoring, left censoring, interval
    censoring, and left truncation. Provides a stand-alone fitting
    function, 'gamlss2'
    family extensions, and Poisson-mixture cure-model wrappers around
    the AFT baselines. Standard AFT estimation, including interval-censored
    responses, uses Newton-Raphson with a modified Cholesky decomposition,
    implemented in both C and Rust; cure fits use BFGS with numerical
    Hessians.
License: GPL (>= 3)
URL: https://keaven.github.io/vldaft/, https://github.com/keaven/vldaft
BugReports: https://github.com/keaven/vldaft/issues
NeedsCompilation: yes
SystemRequirements: Cargo (>= 1.70.0) and rustc, the Rust compiler
    (install from https://rustup.rs). Source installs may need network
    access for Rust crate downloads unless Cargo dependencies are already
    cached.
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports: survival, stats
